<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17510417-15">
               <interp inst="t17510417-15" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510417-15" type="year" value="1751"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510417-15" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17510417"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510417-15" type="date" value="17510417"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17510417-15-off79-c131" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-15-defend164 t17510417-15-off79 t17510417-15-verdict83"></join>
         
               <p>276. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-defend164" type="defendantName">
                     Richard 
                     Peacock 
                  <interp inst="t17510417-15-defend164" type="surname" value="Peacock"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-defend164" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-defend164" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17510417-15-off79" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-off79" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-off79" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one quilted petticoat, value 10 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-victim166" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Stone 
                  <interp inst="t17510417-15-victim166" type="surname" value="Stone"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-victim166" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-victim166" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-15-off79 t17510417-15-victim166"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17510417-15-cd80" type="crimeDate">April 9</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-15-off79 t17510417-15-cd80"></join>. +</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-person167">
                  John 
                  Stone 
               <interp inst="t17510417-15-person167" type="surname" value="Stone"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person167" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person167" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t17510417-15-crimeloc81">Hatton-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17510417-15-crimeloc81" type="placeName" value="Hatton-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17510417-15-crimeloc81" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-15-off79 t17510417-15-crimeloc81"></join>, the prisoner is a <rs id="t17510417-15-deflabel82" type="occupation">soldier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-15-defend164 t17510417-15-deflabel82"></join> and was quarter'd in my house; last Monday sen'night my wife gave him a candle at about 12 at night to go to bed, he went up<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175104170008"></xptr> stairs, but went out and left my doors open all night; the next day we found a trunk broke open, and a white quilted petticoat of my wife's was missing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-person168">
                  Mary 
                  Stone 
               <interp inst="t17510417-15-person168" type="surname" value="Stone"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person168" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person168" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Wife to the prosecutor, confirmed the above.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-person169">
                  John 
                  Bivon 
               <interp inst="t17510417-15-person169" type="surname" value="Bivon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person169" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman in St. Martin's, I and another watchman took the prisoner out of a night cellar with this petticoat under his arm; he had told us different stories about it, where he had it and whose it was.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-person170">
                  George 
                  Graunt 
               <interp inst="t17510417-15-person170" type="surname" value="Graunt"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person170" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person170" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , another watchman, confirmed the testimony of Bivon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510417-15-person171">
                  Peter 
                  Nichols 
               <interp inst="t17510417-15-person171" type="surname" value="Nichols"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person171" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-person171" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             the constable produced the petticoat, the prosecutor and his wife deposed to it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.  I never saw the petticoat in my life before, <rs id="t17510417-15-verdict83" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-verdict83" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17510417-15-punish84" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510417-15-punish84" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-15-defend164 t17510417-15-punish84"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
